post_text:
March 28, 2020

Hello again! Today, I want to clarify what Governor Kelly’s “Stay-at-Home Order” that was issued earlier today means for our current operating procedure.

First of all, the governor’s executive order does not change our Continuous Learning Plan. USD 223 will continue to operate with the online classroom routine that we have in place.

However, due to the more restrictive guidelines in the “Stay-at-Home Order,” USD 223 will not serve meals Monday, March 30 or Tuesday, March 31. I will update you on the status of our meal plan after we hear from the Washington County Healthcare Advisory Council, which is meeting Tuesday, March 31.
text:
March 28, 2020

Hello again! Today, I want to clarify what Governor Kelly’s “Stay-at-Home Order” that was issued earlier today means for our current operating procedure.

First of all, the governor’s executive order does not change our Continuous Learning Plan. USD 223 will continue to operate with the online classroom routine that we have in place.

However, due to the more restrictive guidelines in the “Stay-at-Home Order,” USD 223 will not serve meals Monday, March 30 or Tuesday, March 31. I will update you on the status of our meal plan after we hear from the Washington County Healthcare Advisory Council, which is meeting Tuesday, March 31.

post_text:
Grab and Go meals will continue being offered for all children ages 1-18 at the following locations.
- Linn at the southeast doors of the school and from 11:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. Monday thru Friday
- Hanover at the cafeteria doors from 11:00 a.m. – 12:00 p.m. Monday thru Friday
- Palmer at the rear of the Palmer cafe from 12:15 p.m. to 12:30 p.m. Monday thru Friday
- Barnes at the park shelter house from 12:15 p.m – 12:30 p.m Monday thru Friday.
- USD 108 will be serving the meals at Greenleaf. Students will be able to pick up their meals at the Farmers Coop office from 12:15 p.m. – 12:30 p.m. Parents of these students will need to contact Washington County Schools at (785) 325-2261. They will be able to give you instructions at that time.
If you have not yet answered the survey questions concerning these meals, please go to the following link https://forms.gle/2aoWKeaDV1JKb9nQ9 . It is important to take the time to do so if there is a chance your child will be participating.

USDA requires that students are present at pick-up.

post_text: The Commissioner of Education has recommended that all public schools close their doors for the following week. Therefore, Hanover, Linn, and the Barnes Preschool will not have class for the week of March 16 - March 20. The custodial staff will be the only staff in the buildings so please contact the district office with any questions you may have. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. We appreciate your patience and understanding through this trying time. We will continue to update you with any changes as they happen.

post_text:
The USD #223 Board of Education would like to say congratulations and thank you to all the teachers, staff and students for their hard work and being recognized as a Commissioner’s Award recipient by the Kansas State Department of Education. The Board of Education has decided to extend the winter break by giving faculty members their in-service day off on January 2, 2020 as well as the day off on January 3, 2020 for all staff and students. Second semester will begin Monday morning January 6, 2020. If you have any questions, please contact your building principal.
Have a Merry Christmas and Happy New Year from USD #223.
